rComments: Nice guy, but doesn't actually teach the content. Just spends his time telling you how important exercise is for your health. So don't rely on his lectures to actually learn anything. You have the learn everything by yourself, but the exams aren't too hard. However, he only does one midterm and one exam so they're each worth a lot.

His lectures digress a lot and he tends to just talk about random things which makes it hard to take notes sometimes. What bothers me though is that he will call on people randomly in the online class and call you out if your camera is not on. He doesn't post the lectures after so im just trying to make notes and him calling people out is stressful

He's quite funny, I'll give him that. His slides are very good (concise, easy to follow) so you can easily get away with studying his slides and getting an A+. His lectures are all over the place and can be hard to follow (sometimes it feels like he's just talking bout random stuff). Reading textbook is optional but it can help. Easiest exams

Didn't go to class because he read right off the slides VERY loudly. You can tell he enjoys his material and teaching it though. Final was very hard compared to midterm. Personally wouldn't take again but a very nice guy

Super smart guy and great lecturer. Sit in the back and don't talk or eat unless you want him to call you out. Midterm is easy but the final is a lot tougher and worth 50% so study a lot. The best study tool of all is just focusing and listening in his class. He tells you pretty much everything you need to know. No surprises on the exams.

Great prof. He's a fountain of knowledge. He wants to see his students succeed. He's very concise in his lectures and always goes over material from previous lectures which is a useful teaching strategy uncommon to most profs. If you have an opportunity to have him as a prof you better take it.
SOOO cute. love him. His class is a must take
Dr. Kenny LOVES to figure skate!! I give him 5.0 across the board for his Triple Sow Cow!
Great teacher !  Knew his stuff !  He's the reason why I love teaching anatomy and physiology to my students today !  Thanks !
